And what do I do if I ddon't joust? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 12:03:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=609.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue's vs paladins</span><hr size=1> you dont have to spin, just hit bs as you pass through him.<br>
<br>
paldins are one of those classes I generally find to damn annoying to bother fighting, alot like bards. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uulynvindix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ulyn Vindix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 11:58:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=609.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue's vs paladins</span><hr size=1> Even with &quot;bs jousting,&quot; it is a tough tough assignment.  Preventing people from jousting is really hard in practice.  Depending on his level you might have to deal with uber healing as well as his LoH, and if his weapon is big enough and he jousts you it could be ugly.<br>
<br>
But you never know, go slaughter him.  Rogue power! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uferinal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ferinal</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/12/02 1:47:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=609.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue's vs paladins</span><hr size=1> As a paladin I can give you some insight as to what we try and do against rogues. <br>
<br>
At a certain level a characters MR becomes an issue when dueling. We have a hard time landing our favorite stuns and blinds. For this I try and use a journeyman's walking stick to land a tash. I find that the fight with us paladins is never short and a tash will make things go our way generally.<br>
<br>
I will focus on enstill more than stuns and blind to start with generally to try and keep from being backstabbed. This is the key to the fight for us, or a nice corner if one is available.<br>
<br>
Another important point against rogues is to use a ds. Coldain rings from 8+ stacked with Blazing Vambraces off of Ragefire gives a nice DS or a potion if you allow that.<br>
<br>
Just a few things I use when dueling. Hope it helps you prepare. Pumice stones always help against a buff reliant class and hide against a non-invis seeing opponent is key, they lose you as a target and can't cast on you.<br>
<br>
Have fun.<br>
<br>
<br>
